                <p class="update-date"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> December 30, 2025</p>

                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Thank you for using Mystiq.</strong> Your privacy is important to us. This privacy policy explains how your personal data is collected, used, and protected.</p>
                </div>

                <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
                <p><strong>Company Name:</strong> Teamlify<br>
                <strong>Address:</strong> Istanbul, Turkey<br>
                <strong>Email:</strong> support@mystiq.app<br>
                <strong>Website:</strong> https://mystiq.app</p>

                <h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
                
                <h3>2.1. User-Provided Data</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Email Address:</strong> For account creation and authentication (optional)</li>
                    <li><strong>Name:</strong> For personalized experience (optional)</li>
                    <li><strong>Birth Date, Time, and Location:</strong> For astrology analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Photos:</strong> Coffee cup images for fortune reading</li>
                    <li><strong>Audio Recordings:</strong> For breath detection feature (temporary, not stored)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>2.2. Automatically Collected Data</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Model, operating system, app version</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Feature usage, session duration, interactions</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, language preference, timezone</li>
                    <li><strong>Crash Reports:</strong> Application errors and performance data</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Anonymous usage statistics (Firebase Analytics)</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Service Provision:</strong> Deliver tarot, coffee fortune, astrology, and dream interpretation services</li>
                    <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> Customize and improve user experience</li>
                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Account security and access control</li>
                    <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Important notifications, updates, and support</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Monitor and improve app performance</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> Manage premium subscriptions and purchases</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Fulfill legal requirements</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
                
                <h3>4.1. Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Firebase (Google):</strong> Authentication, database, analytics, and cloud functions</li>
                    <li><strong>Google Cloud Platform:</strong> AI and image analysis services</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment Providers:</strong> App Store (Apple), Google Play (Google) for subscription management</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>4.2. Data Sharing Principles</h3>
                <p>Your data is only shared with third parties in the following cases:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>With your explicit consent</li>
                    <li>As required by law</li>
                    <li>With service providers (only data necessary for service delivery)</li>
                    <li>In case of company merger or acquisition</li>
                </ul>

                <p><strong>Important:</strong> We never sell or rent your data to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

                <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All communications protected with SSL/TLS encryption</li>
                    <li><strong>Secure Storage:</strong> Data stored on Firebase's secure servers</li>
                    <li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Limited personnel access and authentication</li>
                    <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Periodic security vulnerability assessments</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> We only collect necessary data</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>6. Data Retention Period</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> While account is active</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> 24 months</li>
                    <li><strong>Photos (Coffee Fortune):</strong> 30 days after analysis (user can delete)</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Anonymous, 14 months</li>
                    <li><strong>Crash Reports:</strong> 90 days</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>7. User Rights (GDPR)</h2>
                <p>Under GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right of Access:</strong> Know what data is collected about you</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data (right to be forgotten)</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Restriction:</strong> Limit data processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Receive your data in structured format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to data processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Rights Related to Automated Decision-Making:</strong> Object to automated processing</li>
                </ul>

                <p>To exercise these rights, email us at <strong>support@mystiq.app</strong></p>

                <h2>8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                <p>The app uses the following technologies:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> To manage user sessions</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> To collect usage data (anonymous)</li>
                    <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> To save language and theme preferences</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p>Mystiq does not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.</p>

                <h2>10. International Data Transfer</h2>
                <p>Your data may be processed on servers in various countries, including the US and EU, through Firebase and Google Cloud Platform. All transfers comply with GDPR and relevant data protection laws.</p>

                <h2>11. Permissions and Access</h2>
                <p>The app requests the following device permissions:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Camera:</strong> To capture coffee cup photos for fortune reading (optional)</li>
                    <li><strong>Photo Library:</strong> To upload existing photos (optional)</li>
                    <li><strong>Microphone:</strong> For breath detection feature (optional, not recorded)</li>
                    <li><strong>Internet:</strong> To access cloud services (required)</li>
                    <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> For reminders and important updates (optional)</li>
                </ul>

